<p>Overall, radio news salaries (see <xref ref-type="table" rid="table5-1931243112447931">Table 5</xref>) were unchanged in 2009. News directors rose slightly. News reporters, producers, and sports reporters rose, but news and sports anchors fell. Because the largest, highest-paying stations can raise the average salaries out of proportion, the median—or midpoint—is usually considered a better gauge of typical salaries.</p>
